Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Subensemble Acceptance Method 3.0 \[LongDash] Mathematica supplement", \
"Title",ExpressionUUID->"f75de2fa-b327-42f4-bae8-1a93cc6f5a09"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Symbolic implementation of the SAM-3.0 mapping from joint grand-canonical \
cumulants to canonical cumulants at fixed total conserved charge, for an \
arbitrary number of observables and conserved charges.\n\nAccompanies the \
paper:\nR. Poberezhniuk, V. A. Kuznietsov, G. Pihan, V. Vovchenko, ",
 StyleBox["Subensemble Acceptance Method 3.0: General Corrections to \
Cumulants from Exact Conservation Constraints",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 ", arXiv:2607.01783.\n\nTested with Wolfram Mathematica 13 and 14. Released \
under the MIT License. If you use this notebook, please cite the paper above.\
\n\nCopyright (c) 2026 Roman Poberezhniuk, Volodymyr A. Kuznietsov, Gr\
\[EAcute]goire Pihan, Volodymyr Vovchenko"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9911850862738047`*^9, 
  3.9911850939740133`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"21cd42e1-32ef-4f54-96ac-\
b495c748933d"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Scope and assumptions", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"fa1b6d39-3677-4379-b0f6-1beefa83192a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This notebook generates and validates the symbolic SAM-3.0 recursion \
\[LongDash] the algebraic mapping from grand-canonical mixed cumulants to \
canonical cumulants at fixed total charge, to arbitrary order, for any number \
of observables and conserved charges. It does ",
 StyleBox["not",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " reproduce the Hydro-EV numerical baseline, the direct Monte Carlo \
sampling, or the paper figures; those use the joint GCE cumulants produced \
elsewhere as input to the formulas implemented here."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.991267218501528*^9, 
  3.9912672190900784`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"795e91be-c9f5-4a19-81c0-\
0d605bd582cd"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Notation", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"5d767bf2-a7d2-4227-adfd-4589e7442cf6"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["kGCE[{nX, nY, ...}, {mB, mQ, ...}]", "Code"],
 " \[LongDash] a joint grand-canonical mixed cumulant: order nX in the first \
observable, nY in the second, \[Ellipsis], and mB, mQ, \[Ellipsis] in the \
conserved charges. The substitutable symbol behind every ",
 StyleBox["\"Raw\"", "Code"],
 " result.\n",
 StyleBox["KappaCE[{\"X\", \"Y\"}, {nX, nY}, {\"B\", \"Q\"}]", "Code"],
 " \[LongDash] the canonical cumulant ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubsuperscriptBox["\[Kappa]", 
    RowBox[{"nX", " ", "nY"}], 
    RowBox[{"XY", "|", "BQ"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cc76a20d-5d01-4a8c-8415-a0b5e2b0de69"],
 ", i.e. of the observables at fixed total B, Q.\n",
 StyleBox["kB[n]", "Code"],
 " \[LongDash] \[Kappa]_n^B, the total-charge cumulant; appears in the \
single-charge limit rules.\n",
 StyleBox["\[Alpha]", "Code"],
 " \[LongDash] acceptance fraction; ",
 StyleBox["\[Beta] = 1 - \[Alpha]", "Code"],
 "."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.99118618278183*^9, 
  3.9911861958231297`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2e95a546-6674-4cfe-bdc1-\
bbe34c32e4c3"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

