Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["2.3 Two conserved charges (B, Q)", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"22bb0ae3-fab9-4b30-abf3-16dc1c5eefea"],

Cell["\<\
The multi-charge formulas below are fully expanded for the chosen charge \
labels, but their structure is compact. With the charge covariance matrix \
K_{ab} = \[Kappa](B_a, B_b) and the response coefficient A^a = (K^-1)^{ab} \
\[Kappa](X, B_b) (paper Eq. 56), the second-order canonical cumulant is just \
a covariance projection,

  \[Kappa]_2^{X|B} = \[Kappa]_2^X - \[Kappa](X, B_a) A^a   (paper Eq. 60),

and the higher orders are the same projection applied recursively. The \
expanded output is what you substitute or export; for interpretation, read it \
as this K^-1 contraction.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"74be2d9e-e0cc-4024-9ff7-9c0db799a45f"],

Cell["\<\
Diagonal and mixed canonical cumulants with two simultaneously conserved \
charges:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d0d2e215-e91c-44f1-8bc5-fafab069e22b"],

