Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["2.5 SAM-1.0 limit", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"e5236c77-9317-411b-a45d-ed0c692a04f7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "SAM-1.0 assumes a coordinate-space acceptance in a spatially uniform \
thermal system with short-range correlations. Each joint cumulant of the \
observable in the acceptance is then \[Alpha] times the corresponding \
full-system cumulant, with \[Alpha] the acceptance fraction. The rule ",
 StyleBox["SAM1", "Code"],
 " applies this generic-observable scaling, replacing every mixed \
grand-canonical cumulant by its \[Alpha]-scaled full-system counterpart. The \
observable X here is arbitrary \[LongDash] it need not be the conserved \
charge \[LongDash] so the results below still carry mixed (XB) cumulants:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"00dba9c8-9574-41cd-9cfa-209c44c64722"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
