Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["2.6 Binomial acceptance limit", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"7c1a0379-0bc2-40c2-811e-f36971ba11e7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Under independent Bernoulli sampling with probability \[Alpha], the \
canonical cumulants at fixed B_tot become those of a binomial distribution, \
with all ",
 StyleBox["kB[n >= 2]", "Code"],
 " cancelling \[LongDash] the result depends only on \[Kappa]_1^B and \
\[Alpha], not on the equation of state. This is the check SAM-2.0 fails and \
SAM-3.0 passes. ",
 StyleBox["BinomialAcceptance", "Code"],
 " applies to the single-observable, single-charge case (",
 StyleBox["d = s = 1", "Code"],
 "); outputs use \[Beta] = 1 - \[Alpha]. Here the observable is the accepted \
conserved charge itself, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"X", "=", 
    SubscriptBox["B", "in"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c289bc7a-6b53-40f1-a815-4f4c3ae3f9b1"],
 ", drawn by Bernoulli sampling from the fixed total ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["B", "tot"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bdda37e5-3734-4848-a464-10c41fef0300"],
 "."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9911854901309757`*^9, 
  3.991185510606164*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"508b008e-0ffc-4990-bf90-\
30ff703916ae"],

